Marinate the chicken and sausages in the soy sauce and 1 teaspoon salt and set aside. Heat sesame oil in a large, nonstick wok. Stir fry the ginger until fragrant. Add the sausages and chicken and stir fry until brown. Add the mushrooms and fry for another 3 minutes. Stir in the rice and season with salt and pepper. Transfer the mixture to a rice cooker and add water. When rice is cooked, garnish with chopped coriander and spring onions. Serve.